title: Non Coprime Sequences
text: You are given two integers,nandm.Find and print the number of sequences of length n which satisfy:All elements of the sequence are positive divisors of mFor any two adjacent elements, say p and q, there exists at least one prime which divides both of them.Print the number of such sequences modulo 109+7InputThe only line of input contains two integers, n and m.Constraints0 < n ≤ 1050 < m ≤ 1018OutputPrint the number of valid sequences modulo 109+7ExampleInput:2 10Output:7Print the number of such sequences modulo10^9 + 7
